      "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/p/50afbb/{size}.png",
      "created_at": "2024-05-30T01:32:51.573Z",
      "cooked": "<p>When I start my TrainingPeaks imported WOD, it always starts in Erg.  I prefer to use Slope, so I switch it over right at the beginning.  However, if I forget, and I\u2019ve started pedaling, it often won\u2019t switch Slope on properly and it acts like I\u2019m in a 30/44 or something with almost no resistance on the pedals even in my hardest gear and with a high slope %. To fix this, I have to kill the app, stop the trainer, reopen TrainerDay, restart the workout, and switch to Slope before I pedal.  Even this doesn\u2019t always work properly and sometimes I have to do this multiple times before it recognizes Slope.  Am I doing something wrong or is there an easier way?</p>\n<p>TrainerDay running on iPad app connected to Tacx Neo OG.</p>\n<p>Thanks for your help!</p>",
