      "created_at": "2024-05-30T08:03:45.473Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Hello, sorry I have to ask.  There is another \u201cfamous\u201d pbase that is active on a popular cycling forum is that you by chance?  You don\u2019t have to answer <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\">  Anyway no this sounds like a bug or issue.  Can you repeat this easily, meaning if you worked with my developer and he was reviewing logs in real time could he see this in a reasonable amount of time?</p>\n<p>Do you happen to have an Android device you can test on?  I have a Neo but my bike is getting repaired (cracked frame) and don\u2019t know how to mount my wheel through MTB or Bmx on the Neo 2T to see if I can duplicate.  I can and probably should give my Neo to my tester but this might be specific to your trainer or the OG version (I assume the OG is the original Neo).  While I don\u2019t like my Wahoo any more than Neo, I test and end up using the kickr. Easier to set it up is why and I am lazy.</p>",
